The SSC Standing Committees are:
(1) University Committee on Student Life Executive Committee: coordinates the activities of the SSC and its committees and subcommittees;
(2) Student Grievance Committee: focuses upon disputes between student organizations, student or residence hall councils, and is responsible for supervising and administrating the SSC censure procedures;
(3) Committee on Rules and Organization: reviews proposals to amend or adopt any Rules of Procedure of the SSC, the UCSL, and any of their committees, and periodically reviews the organizational policies of University student government.

UCSL Standing Committees:
(1) Committee on Academic Services: handles matters concerning academically-related support services and programs provided by the University to students;
(2) All Square Student Budget Allocation Committee (ASSBAC): establishes the criteria under which student organizations may receive All-Square funding, allocates such funding to student organizations, and monitors the use of allocated funds; 
(3) Committee on External Affair: considers all matters relating to the SSC/UCSL's association with external organizations; 
(4) Committee on Graduate Affairs: considers all matters relating to the academic and extracurricular life of students enrolled in the graduate and professional schools of the University; (5) Committee on Student Services: considers non-academic matters relating to the general well-being and comfort of the NYU students.

UCSL Ad-Hoc Committees:
(1) Committee on Alumni Relations: considers issues concerning the relationship between current students and alumni;
(2) Student Health Advisory Board: considers all matters relating to the University Health Center and shall take special interest in informing the student body about the services that the center provides
